Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Pricetack enables online sellers to offer merchandise under a falling price schedule. With Pricetack's selling format, merchants list items with a starting price that declines over time. Buyers can purchase immediately or wait for a discount. However waiting risks losing the item to another buyer. Automatic markdown pricing is good for both used and new items with limited supply. It is especially good for items that lose value over time or have an expiration date. Like standard auctions, falling price schedules can serve as a price discovery mechanism. This pricing format is particularly lends itself well to customer and prospect engagement since prices are constantly changing and items are coming onto the market as well as leaving.

Description: UrbanCCD promotes research and creates computational research tools for researchers, government agencies, architectural firms, and more.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: UrbanCCD (Urban Center for Computation and Data) promotes research and creates computational research tools for academic researchers, government agencies, architectural firms, private enterprises, and civic volunteers. The center aims to identify, collaborate, and address challenges and opportunities in urban science. It builds and participates in an interdisciplinary community of urban scientists, researchers, policy makers, and citizens. The center provides tools and methods that gather and integrate data from a variety of sources, including databases, scientific simulations, and mobile and fixed sensors. Its research tools include Array of Things (AoT): a network of interactive, modular sensor boxes that collect real-time data on a cityâs environment, infrastructure, and activity for research and public use; Plenario: a tool that enables scientists to select a geographic area, determine what data is available about that area, and extract an integrated collection of selected data sets for a particular time period for further analysis; WindyGrid: an internal real-time situational awareness data system; and LakeSim: an open workflow framework designed to integrate city design and configuration tools with computational modeling tools. UrbanCCD has academic and research center partners, federal and foundation partners, and public and industry partners. UrbanCCD is based in Chicago, Illinois.

There are so many options, people are flaky...really, is there anything worse than organizing an event? Say hello to CitySwarm. CitySwarm provides a better way to explore Chicago and opens the door to unique, memorable experiences in the best city in the world. CitySwarm events are: > Social Since CitySwarm caters to the young professional demographic living in Chicago, our events also provide an incredible social opportunity for guests to meet new people with whom they have things in common. Whether you're interested in networking socially or professionally, or simply being among a group of your peers, it's easy to have fun and meet friendly people at a CitySwarm event. > Hassle-Free CitySwarm events provide everything you need for a great experience without any of the hassle. We take care of all the little details - from transportation to tickets to food and beverage and everything in between. All you need to do is purchase your ticket, show up, and have a great time! > Unique CitySwarm offers experiences that you just can't get every day! Our team works hard to create unforgettable events spanning recreation, culture, dining and nightlife, digging up private access and exclusive opportunities along the way to ensure your experience is special and memorable. > High-Value Because we travel in a group, we're able to negotiate the best rates for every activity and pass the savings on to you. Combine this with everything we've mentioned above, and you can rest assured that the value of a CitySwarm event will far exceed your expectations. In addition to our regularly-offered experiences, we also offer periodic non-for-profit group volunteering events to help our members give back to the community in an easy and fun way. We support local causes through our cross-promotion program.
